          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Process Section -->
      <div class="bg-primary-light border-primary mb-12 rounded-lg border p-6">
        <h3 class="text-primaryBlue mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">How We Deliver These Services</h3>
        <p class="text-gray leading-relaxed">
          The process begins with data collection from clients, including compound-specific details, manufacturing
          processes, and existing toxicological data. Our toxicologists analyze this data alongside public databases
          (e.g., PubChem, ECHA, TOXNET) to derive ADE/PDE/OEL values and categorize compounds into OEB bands. For
          cleaning validation, we calculate residue limits and develop containment strategies. Safety Assessment Reports
          (SAR) are prepared for finished formulations, integrating toxicological thresholds and regulatory
          requirements. MSDS/SDS documents are authored by compiling data into the 16-section GHS format, ensuring
          compliance with region-specific regulations. The entire process, typically spanning 2‚Äì4 weeks, involves
          iterative reviews, client collaboration, and regulatory submission support to ensure GMP and audit readiness.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Regulatory and Certifications Section -->
      <div class="bg-secondary-light2 border-secondary mb-12 rounded-lg border p-6">
        <h3 class="text-primaryBlue mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">Regulatory Compliance and Certifications</h3>
        <p class="text-gray leading-relaxed">
          Our services adhere to stringent global regulatory standards, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-gray mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>EMA Guidelines on PDE/ADE:</strong> For health-based exposure limits in cleaning validation.</li>
          <li><strong>ICH Q3D:</strong> Elemental impurities assessment for pharmaceuticals.</li>
          <li><strong>REACH & GHS Compliance:</strong> For chemical safety and classification in the EU.</li>
          <li><strong>OSHA Hazard Communication Standards:</strong> For workplace safety in the US.</li>
          <li><strong>EU Regulation No 1272/2008 (CLP):</strong> For classification, labeling, and packaging.</li>
          <li><strong>WHO, ISPE, and GMP Guidelines:</strong> For quality risk management and manufacturing.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray leading-relaxed">
          Our team ensures compliance through expertise in toxicology, regulatory affairs, and occupational safety,
          supported by certifications in GHS, REACH, and OSHA standards. We provide audit-ready documentation and assist
          with regulatory submissions to streamline approvals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Conclusion Section -->
      <div class="bg-primary-light border-primary mb-12 rounded-lg border p-6">
        <h3 class="text-primaryBlue mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">Conclusion</h3>
        <p class="text-gray leading-relaxed">
          Indivirtus‚Äô toxicological and safety documentation services empower pharmaceutical manufacturers, CROs, and
          biotech firms to achieve regulatory compliance, ensure workplace safety, and mitigate risks. By delivering
          precise ADE/PDE/OEL calculations, comprehensive Safety Assessment Reports, and GHS-compliant SDS documents, we
          support GMP-compliant operations and global market access. Our expertise in toxicology and regulatory affairs
          ensures that your manufacturing processes meet the highest safety and quality standards.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <!-- Call to Action Section -->
    <div class="bg-secondary-light border-secondary mb-12 border p-6 text-center">
      <h3 class="text-primaryBlue mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">Ready to Ensure Safety and Compliance?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray mb-4">Partner with Indivirtus for expert toxicological and regulatory support.</p>
      <BTN btnLink="/contact-us" btnClass="button" btnText="Contact Us Today" />
    </div>

    <section class="maxwidth">
      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <Faq faqs={mainEntity} />
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
